body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 docs audit: scripts/release/docs-skills-gate.mjs splits link targets on [?#], so FILE.md#heading links only verify the file exists — dead anchors are ungated. All 12 current anchor links were verified by hand (none broken); this closes the gap for future ones.\n\n## Approach\nIn the gate, when a relative link carries a fragment: read the target file, slugify its headings (GitHub slugger rules — lowercase, strip punctuation, spaces→dashes, dedupe with -1 suffixes), and assert the fragment matches. While touching docs, break the wall-of-text paragraphs into bullets: EXTENSIONS.md line 89 (~4600 chars) and line 114; COMMANDS.md lines 612 and 627.\n\n## Definition of done\nGate fails on a seeded dead anchor and passes on the current tree; the four wall-of-text paragraphs are restructured; gate runtime stays negligible in CI static gates."
